Description: Mould-made pottery Frog-Type lamp with a sharply carinated body. The filling-hole area is flanked by oval depressions; above the filling-hole area are the heads of Helios and Selene face-to-face, with an oval depression over each head. The base is undefined; there is a large impressed swastika below.
Bibliographic references: Lamp / Catalogue of the Lamps in the British Museum (Q2127.bis)
